  "name": "Capacitive Touch Latch",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Capacitive Touch Latch",
    "description": "Touch the metal pad to turn the red LED on and keep it on after you lift your finger. Your touch starts an NPN switch (USB → T → 470Ω → LED → collector); a 100kΩ resistor from collector back to base latches the transistor on. Press the reset tact button to short the base to ground and turn the LED off. Compare lesson 58 (hold tact to stay on), lesson 71 (NMOS), and lesson 79 (touch without latch). Touch pad at 90°; NPN at 0°; reset tact at 90°."
  },
